text:
80% of people living with diabetes are diagnosed;
80% have good control of glycaemia;
80% of people with diagnosed diabetes have good control of blood pressure;
60% of people with diabetes of 40 years or older receive statins; and
100% of people with type 1 diabetes have access to affordable insulin and blood glucose 
self-monitoring.
Screen people with diabetes for proteinuria and treat with angiotensin-converting-enzyme 
inhibitor to prevent or delay kidney disease.
